related_questions.question: Which is better, black tea or green tea?
related_questions.snippet: Both green tea and black tea can be a part of a balanced diet and provide health benefits. Green tea is thought to be better for you because of its high antioxidant activity from catechins. It is also lower in caffeine than black tea. So if you're sensitive to caffeine, green tea may be a better bet.

buttons.subtitle: What Does Black Tea Do To Your Body?
buttons.title: BLACK TEA - Uses, Side Effects, and More - WebMD
buttons.snippet: Black tea contains 2% to 4% caffeine, which affects thinking and alertness. It also contains antioxidants and other substances that might help protect the heart and blood vessels. It has different properties than green tea, which is made from the fresh leaves of the same plant.

buttons.title: How to brew the perfect Black Tea? - Lipton

Milk in black tea is a classic British thing. However, if you want to warm up your tea why not try adding some spice and brew your own Spiced Indian Chai?
